.bat: the file extension used for a batch script

set: used to see all variables
    and used to set a variable:
        ex. 'set message=hello'
REM: used to create a comment
    ex. 'REM This is a Comment'
echo: used to print something to the console
    ex. 'echo This messsage'
@echo off: only displays what is being printed out
@echo on: displays every line of the script
pause: pauses the script and waits for user input
variable access: you can use two '%' to access a variable
    ex. '%variable%'